You are building WorldView, a geospatial intelligence dashboard.

GENERAL BEHAVIOR
- Before writing any code, state your plan in 3-5 bullet points
- Never hardcode API keys, URLs with secrets, or credentials — use .env variables
- Never mock or fake data — if a real API endpoint exists, use it
- If you are unsure about a Cesium API, say so rather than guessing
- Always clean up setInterval, event listeners, and Cesium entities on unmount
- Keep each file under 200 lines — split into smaller modules if needed

CODE STYLE
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any` types
- Functional React components only, no class components
- All Cesium viewer access via Zustand store (never pass viewer as a prop)
- Data fetchers live in src/dataFetchers/ and export a single custom hook
- All environment variables prefixed with VITE_ and documented in .env.example

WHAT TO AVOID
- Do not install unnecessary dependencies
- Do not create a backend or proxy server unless explicitly asked
- Do not use placeholder/lorem ipsum data
- Do not skip error handling on fetch calls
- Do not rewrite files from previous phases unless asked

DONE.md
- At the end of every phase, update DONE.md
- Mark the phase complete, note any deviations from CONTEXT.md
- Add any new environment variables to the "Required Keys" section
PHASES 11-15 SPECIFIC RULES
- Never remove working code from Phases 1-10 — only extend
- All new PostProcessStages must be cleaned up on mode change
- Sliders must debounce at 16ms to avoid per-frame Zustand updates
- TensorFlow.js must load lazily — never block globe initialization
- localStorage usage is permitted only for Scenes (Phase 14)
- New layers follow exact same hook pattern as useAircraftLayer()
- Performance budget: total entities must stay under 1500 across all layers
